step.context:
\text{If $ A = [a_{ij}]_{m \times n}$ and } B = [b_{ij}]_{m \times n} 
\text{ are any two matrices,}\\
\text{then, are all the following conclusions correct?}

step.reason:
P_{m \times n}- Q_{m \times n} = D_{m \times n} = [d_{ij}]_{m \times n}\text{ where,}\\
d_{ij} = p_{ij} - q_{ij} \, (\forall \text{ possible ij values)}. \\
\text{Thus, corresponding elements are subtracted.}

\text{If, } X = [x_{ij}]_{\,m\times n} \text{ and k is a scalar then,}\\
\text{kX is another matrix of order m\times n}\\
\text{such that }
kX = [k(x_{ij})]_{\,m\times n}
